{ Hello and welcome to my study! 👋

This is an interactive study on how to play the Scotch Gambit! 🥳

You will learn the basics of how to play it, a ton a variations, and tools to combat all the tricks black will throw at us! 🤾

History Lesson! 🗺️:

"The Scotch Gambit was popularized by Paul Morphy and--"

This is a chess lesson, not a history lesson!

Do you want to win in less than ten move? 😃

Do you want to play a fun gambit that has been around for HUNDREDS OF YEARS! 🥳

Do you want to topple of and die if black knows what to do? 🤔 NO! 😡

Then let's get started! 🏁

Psst, this entire repertoire is available in Noctie and ready for you to practice! https://go.noctie.ai/scotch-gambit

Start with 1.e4! }
1. e4 { This is the starting move for most gambits. 🎲 } 1... e5 { Attack! } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gg1f3] } 2. Nf3 { [%csl Re5][%cal Rf3e5] } 2... Nc6 { Transpose to ➡️ the Scotch Game! } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gd2d4] } 3. d4 { The Scotch Game! } 3... exd4 { Instead of taking the pawn, can you develop a piece instead? } 4. Bc4 { This is the Scotch Gambit! Learn the next chapters and you will be able to CRUSH you opponents with this nasty repetoire! 😄 } *


