{ Charge the Knight!!! 🫵 } { [%csl Re5][%cal Re4e5] }
2. e5 d5 { Our bishop is under threat! 😱 We may be tempted to play En Passent 🥖, but how can we pin the knight instead? } { [%csl Rc4,Re8][%cal Rd5c4,Rb5e8] } 3. Bb5 { Yup. } { [%csl Re8][%cal Rb5e8] } 3... Ne4 { Gets their knight out of trouble. How can we make use of the pinned knight? } { [%csl Re8][%cal Rb5e8] } 4. Nxd4 { Yes! Material is now even! } 4... Bd7 { We have to take the knight, but with what... } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Bc6d4] } 5. Bxc6 { Yes! 🤯 This lets our awesome knight still be awesome! } 5... bxc6 { Castle. 🏰 } { [%csl Gg1][%cal Ge1g1] } 6. O-O Bc5 { How can we get this pesky knight away? 🪰👊 } { [%csl Re4] } 7. f3 { Not a lotta options. } { [%csl Rd6,Rf6,Rc3,Rc5,Rg3,Rf2,Rd2,Gg5] } 7... Ng5 { How should we re-enforce our knight? } { [%csl Rd4] } 8. Be3 { Yep! This position is equal, but then again, black basically played all stockfish moves. Not gonna happen in a game! (well...) 🤪 } *


